Policy.acknowledgement_statement:
Approved Users are expected to acknowledge the Submitting Investigators who submitted data from the original study, the National Cancer Institute (NCI) as the primary funding organization that supported the original work, and the dbGaP and any other relevant repositories. The acknowledgment statement must include the dbGaP accession number to the specific version of the dataset(s) analyzed.
The original work was supported in part by grants from the National Cancer Institute (NCI) Clinical Proteomic Tumor Analysis Consortium grants NIH/NCI U24 CA210986 (to SAC and MAG), NIH/NCI U01 CA214125 (to SAC and MJE), NIH/NCI U24 CA210979 (to DRM) and NIH/NCI U24 CA210954 (to BZ). Also by CPRIT established investigator award CPRIT RR140033 to MJE, and NIH/NCI U10 CA180860 to MJE and DM, U54 CA224076 to MTL, T32 CA203690 (to JTL), as well as NIH/NCI U54 CA233223 and P30 CA125123 to Baylor College of Medicine Cancer Center. Tissue acquisition was also initially supported by a BCRF grant to MJE. MJE is a Susan G. Komen Scholar and a McNair Medical Foundation Scholar. The project also received philanthropic support from Harold & Patricia Korell and Ralph and Lisa Eads. Tissue analysis was also supported by the Baylor Breast Cancer SPORE P50 CA186784. We also thank the Alvin J. Siteman Caner Center at Washington University School of Medicine and Barnes-Jewish Hospital in St. Louis, MO. and the Institute of Clinical and Translational Sciences (ICTS) at Washington University in St. Louis, for the use of the Tissue Procurement Core. The Siteman Cancer Center is supported in part by an NCI Cancer Center Support Grant #P30 CA091842 and the ICTS is funded by the National Institutes of Health’s NCATS Clinical and Translational Science Award (CTSA) program grant UL1 TR002345 National Cancer Institute of the National Institutes of Health under Award Number K12 CA167540 (to FOA).
